{"author":{"id":"69a73b59e8bca0653e9174a374f9f55c998c9a49750b37bad6bd3960e96b7ca3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1617048860,"nonce":"606NsucM8TXqiM8k3UDJ7CT5SeY=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU4NDM3NjU1MjE=","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/524","origin":"github"},"title":"Give DigestType aliases for common names of algorithms","message":"The constant changes to `DigestType`'s names \u0026 values are getting annoying, and the names are getting less intuitive.  It would be nice if the enum had aliases ([members with different names but the same value](https://docs.python.org/3/library/enum.html#duplicating-enum-members-and-values)) allowing the use of more common names of digest algorithms as alternatives to the canonical names — for example, allowing `DigestType.SHA1` as an alias for `DigestType.sha1` and allowing `DigestType.sha256` \u0026 `DigestType.SHA256` as aliases for `DigestType.sha2_256`.\n\n@satra How would we do this without messing up the JSON Schema \u0026 JSON-LD stuff?","files":null}]}